"footnotes":[
[
"GABHS = group A β-hemolytic streptococci; TSS = toxic shock syndrome."
],
[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"a"
]
},
"Diagnosis is considered confirmed when fever, hypotension, and rash with involvement of three or more organ systems listed and negative serologic and cerebrospinal fluid results listed are all present."
],
[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"sup",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"b"
]
},
"A definite case is defined by the isolation of GABHS from a sterile site; hypotension with systolic blood pressure ≤90 mm Hg; plus the presence of two or more of the clinical findings listed."
],
